---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Icon from '../components/Icon.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About John"
  description="John Westley has held revenue leadership roles most consultants only advise from — CRO, VP Sales, VP Marketing, CEO. He diagnoses what others prescribe."
>
  <Nav />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#090e1a] pt-28 sm:pt-32 pb-16 sm:pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr_380px] gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="text-[11px] sm:text-[12px] font-medium text-white/30 uppercase tracking-[0.1em] mb-6">About John Westley</p>
          <h1 class="text-[36px] sm:text-[48px] md:text-[60px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.03em] text-white leading-[1.05] mb-6">
            He's been in every seat at the table
          </h1>
          <p class="text-[16px] sm:text-[18px] text-white/60 leading-relaxed mb-8 sm:mb-10">
            Most revenue consultants have read about the seats. John has held them —
            CRO, VP Sales, VP Marketing, CEO. That changes what he sees, and what he knows to fix.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
            {[
              { metric: "$84M", label: "Revenue scaled from $6M starting point" },
              { metric: "117%", label: "Net Revenue Retention achieved" },
              { metric: "$3.5M", label: "Recovered in six months from structural fix" },
              { metric: "24%", label: "Unit sales lift without headcount increase" },
            ].map(item => (
              <div data-counter class="opacity-0 flex items-center gap-4 sm:gap-5 card-ring-dark rounded-[10px] px-5 sm:px-6 py-4">
                <span class="text-[24px] sm:text-[28px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.03em] text-white min-w-[72px] sm:min-w-[80px]">{item.metric}</span>
                <span class="text-[12px] sm:text-[13px] text-white/50 leading-snug">{item.label}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- John's photo -->
        <div class="relative mt-6 md:mt-0">
          <div class="card-ring-dark rounded-[16px] overflow-hidden aspect-[3/4]">
            <img
              src="/images/john-westley.webp"
              alt="John Westley"
              class="w-full h-full object-cover object-center"
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
            />
          </div>
          <!-- Name badge -->
          <div class="absolute -bottom-4 left-4 sm:left-6 right-4 sm:right-6 card-ring-dark rounded-[10px] px-4 sm:px-5 py-4 bg-[#090e1a]/90 backdrop-blur-sm">
            <p class="text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] font-semibold text-white">John Westley</p>
            <p class="text-[12px] sm:text-[13px] text-white/40">Founder, Growth That Holds</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Story -->
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-24">
      <div class="max-w-3xl" data-reveal>
        <p class="text-[11px] sm:text-[12px] font-medium text-[#888888] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] mb-6">Background</p>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-7 sm:gap-8 text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            John didn't start as a consultant. He started as the person responsible for the number.
            CRO. VP Sales. VP Marketing. CEO. For years, he was in the room when the forecast missed,
            when pipeline dried up, when a good quarter didn't repeat. He owned those moments — the
            ones that show you what's actually broken.
          </p>
          <p>
            What he kept finding was this: the problem wasn't the people. It wasn't bad leads or a
            weak product. It was something structural — a gap in how the revenue motion was designed.
            A broken handoff. A retention motion that didn't exist. A comp plan that accidentally
            rewarded the wrong behavior. Things that weren't visible from any one seat in the room,
            but obvious when you'd sat in all of them.
          </p>
          <p>
            He started seeing the same pattern in company after company. Different industries, different
            sizes, different teams — same structural taxes. And the advice those companies were getting
            from the outside? Almost always tactical. Almost always addressed the symptom, not the cause.
          </p>

          <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-[#2563eb] pl-5 sm:pl-6 py-1 my-2">
            <p class="text-[17px] sm:text-[18px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.02em] text-[#171717] leading-[1.3] not-italic">
              "The structural problem doesn't care how hard the team is working. It just keeps taking its cut."
            </p>
          </blockquote>

          <p>
            Growth That Holds exists because fixing the structure is different from optimizing the execution.
            It requires a different kind of diagnosis. John built the practice around that insight —
            and around staying through implementation until the new motion actually holds.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Makes This Different -->
  <section class="bg-[#fafafa] border-y border-black/[0.06]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-24">
      <div class="mb-10 sm:mb-12" data-reveal>
        <p class="text-[11px] sm:text-[12px] font-medium text-[#888888] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] mb-4">Why It's Different</p>
        <h2 class="text-[28px] sm:text-[36px] md:text-[44px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.025em] text-[#171717] leading-[1.1] max-w-2xl">
          He diagnoses.<br />Most consultants prescribe.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-5 sm:gap-6" data-reveal-group>
        {[
          {
            title: "Practitioner perspective",
            icon: "users",
            body: "John has owned P&L, managed quota-carrying teams, and been responsible for the number. That gives him a different lens than someone who has only advised from the outside."
          },
          {
            title: "Cross-functional view",
            icon: "chart",
            body: "Having sat in marketing, sales, and CRO roles, he doesn't see the revenue motion from one function. He sees how they're supposed to connect — and where they're not."
          },
          {
            title: "Stays through implementation",
            icon: "rebuild",
            body: "The diagnosis is valuable. The implementation is where value is created. John stays through both — not because it's billable time, but because a deck without execution is just a deck."
          },
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="card-ring rounded-[10px] p-6 sm:p-7 bg-white">
            <div class="icon-ring mb-4">
              <Icon name={item.icon} size={20} />
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-[17px] sm:text-[18px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.02em] text-[#171717] mb-3">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-[13px] sm:text-[14px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed">{item.body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Roles held -->
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-24">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 sm:gap-16 items-start">
        <div data-reveal>
          <p class="text-[11px] sm:text-[12px] font-medium text-[#888888] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] mb-5">Experience</p>
          <h2 class="text-[26px] sm:text-[32px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.025em] text-[#171717] leading-[1.1] mb-6">
            Every seat in the revenue room
          </h2>
          <p class="text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed mb-5">
            The reason John can diagnose structural problems across the full revenue journey is that
            he's been accountable for each part of it — from demand generation through close,
            through expansion, through the P&amp;L.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed">
            That isn't a portfolio point. It's what makes the diagnosis accurate.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="120">
          {[
            {
              role: "Chief Revenue Officer",
              detail: "Full revenue accountability — marketing, sales, CS, RevOps. Owned the number.",
              icon: "trending-up"
            },
            {
              role: "VP of Sales",
              detail: "Quota-carrying team management. Pipeline, close rates, forecast, comp design.",
              icon: "chart"
            },
            {
              role: "VP of Marketing",
              detail: "Demand gen, brand, product marketing. Owned pipeline contribution.",
              icon: "users"
            },
            {
              role: "Chief Executive Officer",
              detail: "P&L ownership. Revenue strategy + organizational design for growth.",
              icon: "star"
            },
          ].map(item => (
            <div class="card-ring rounded-[10px] px-5 sm:px-6 py-4 sm:py-5 bg-white flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="icon-ring flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                <Icon name={item.icon} size={18} />
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] font-semibold text-[#171717] mb-1">{item.role}</h3>
                <p class="text-[12px] sm:text-[13px] text-[#888888] leading-relaxed">{item.detail}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Philosophy / Quote -->
  <section class="bg-[#090e1a]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center" data-reveal>
        <p class="text-[11px] sm:text-[12px] font-medium text-white/30 uppercase tracking-[0.1em] mb-8">Philosophy</p>
        <blockquote class="text-[22px] sm:text-[28px] md:text-[36px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.025em] text-white leading-[1.15] mb-8">
          "Revenue that holds isn't built by working harder. It's built by removing what's structurally in the way."
        </blockquote>
        <p class="text-[14px] sm:text-[15px] text-white/40">— John Westley</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-white border-t border-black/[0.06]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-20 text-center">
      <div class="max-w-xl mx-auto" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="text-[26px] sm:text-[32px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.025em] text-[#171717] leading-[1.1] mb-5">
          Ready to talk?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-[15px] sm:text-[16px] text-[#4d4d4d] leading-relaxed mb-8">
          One honest conversation is where every engagement starts. Bring your situation —
          John will tell you quickly whether this is the right fit.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/book"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 sm:px-7 py-3.5 sm:py-4 bg-[#171717] text-white text-[14px] sm:text-[15px] font-medium rounded-[6px] hover:bg-[#2a2a2a] transition-colors"
        >
          Book a Conversation
          <Icon name="arrow-right" size={14} />
        </a>
        <p class="text-[12px] sm:text-[13px] text-[#888888] mt-4">Free · 45 minutes · No prep required</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
